<3 Valentines Day Trunk and Treasure Sale <3
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Come on Sunday, February 12th, to our Valentines Day Trunk and Treasure Sale brought to you by the fellows and close affiliates at the" Not in Public" Warehouse Space! Take it easy this month, procrastinate, and don't buy anything special for that special someone that you love! Instead, wait until the 12th and check out all of the little treasures that our amazing vendors have made in order to sell to you, just in time for Valentines Day! We will have all day tunes, fun morning drinks, some tasty treats available, some intricate jewelry being sold, some bags and such for your many items to hold, artsy endeavors that are fun to look at and other random great things like treats and bows for your furry little animals! Here are some of our featured vendors: Daniel Barron: "Murder Bags" This talented artist makes the most amazing messenger bags. They are handmade and painted inside and out. He describes them as, "Cool bags that hold a lot of Stuff." You can check them out at: www.facebook.com/killingit187 Lynda Lucas: "Vein Jewelry" This beautiful lady creates unisex, vintage, antique and conceptual art for wear. You can check out her treasures at: http://veinjewelry.tumblr.com/ Christina Hernandez: "Little Nugget Accessories" This little lady is all over the map with her imaginative, stylish and cute creations. She makes a wide array of dog bows for every sized cuddly pet. She also creates beautiful leather/feather clip in hair accessories. Come check out these nuggets in person! Ashley Bart: "Chola- Hipster Jewelry" I create one of a kind large hooped, chain linked, vintage trinket-ed, and feathered jewelry. If your lady is a little bit gangsta and a little bit retro she will love my stuff! :) Nicole Adee Dreyfus: Terrariums This lady creates green beauty with her glass held nature! Terrariums of different shapes and sizes. Come see for yourself! Megan Stacy: "Salty Fox" Megan here creates some gorgeous jewelry for "foxy earthlings". Some of the materials that she uses include: brass, pyrite, gold, recycled leather, gems, chains, and of course, TREASURES! Check out her creations:www.saltyfox.etsy.com Niki Horton: "Miss Niki" This talented artisan dabbles in all sorts of artistic creations from one of a kind jewelry to bad ass little pocket knives. She is gearing up for our little show and promises to impress! Check out the goods: http://www.etsy.com/shop/missnikimakesthings Christian Thormann: Photography Prints This crazy/cool native New Yorker will have prints available from the different adventures of his life. Come check out his many styles of photos! :) Spy on him first: http://ilovenymorethanyou.tumblr.com/ Allison Shear: Dry Haircuts Come get cleaned up with a dry haircut by this talented fox of a hairstylist! By day she works at a hit salon and by Feb 12th she will be giving discounted rate dry haircuts for around 20$. Requirements for haircut: show up with clean hair! She will do the rest! Eric Otto: "Raw Goods" Come check out this man's artsy products and collectible goods in the large back room of the space. Look at this: website: www.shoprawgoods.com Tell some friends and HOPE TO SEE YOU THERE! If you are a vendor that would like to be part of our show shoot me and e-mail with a little bit about yourself and your treasures at: ashleylynnbart@gmail.com
Sunday, February 12, 2012, 11 AM - 6 PM in PST
N.I.P Warehouse,17th St. and Capp,San Francisco,California,United States

Panda Lounge Sky Bar 2013
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
The panda Peters are super stoked to bring the Panda Lounge back to the playa this year! If you were a patron during our inaugural outing you know what we're all about: a chance to escape the hustle and bustle of Black Rock City. Fancy drinks, funky beats, and panoramic views of the playa combine to create an experience that's a bit more intimate and refined than your typical Burning Man fare. Come for a drink and stay for a while - we tend to focus on longer, more involved sets from fewer, higher quality, and quite often sexier DJs. Here is our schedule this year: Monday Day: Andy Warren Monday Night: Dan Sherman Wednesday Day: Dan Sherman Wednesday Night: MightyKat 5pm-8pm Guada 8pm - sunrise Thursday Day: Hoj Thursday Night: atish Friday Day: Sneak-E Pete 12-5pm Tim 4-5pm Bo 5pm - sunset Saturday Day: Jordy noon-3pm Mark Slee Saturday Night: Slee & Guests Sunday: Surprises! Day parties start around noon and go through sunset. Night parties start after dinner and go through sunrise. It's going to look something like this: www.thepandalounge.com We'll be right on the corner so you can't miss us. <3

Tap Into Your Subconscious, Rewrite Beliefs, Recreate Reality - EFT Circle
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
EFT is a synthesis of breath-awareness, acupressure, and cognitive behavioral therapy. EFT is likened to an advanced form of self-hypnosis. It runs self-love, self-forgiveness, and self-acceptance through your body's electrical system until your reality shifts. It is truly a magical tool as well as a practical tool. I invite you to use EFT to heal your heart, align with your life purpose, and transform old patterns that no longer serve you. Each class will cover a different topic including: life purpose, sexuality, love and relationships, creativity, abundance, physical pain, chronic illness, or any topic suggested by the class. This class will feature group work, partner skill building, and question and discussion. Please bring yourself and your willingness to heal. $10-$20 suggested donation or your earnest presence.

Charity Sloshball Tournament
Dustin went
Katie, Meena, Christina and I (Marina) are currently training to participate in the Nike Women's Half Marathon (Oct. 21st) on behalf of Team in Training. The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society's Team In Training is the largest endurance training program in the US and provides coaching and training in exchange for raising money towards finding a cure for leukemia and lymphoma. We EACH need to raise $2500 in order to complete this event in honor of all individuals who are battling blood cancers, so we're turning to all you charitable individuals to help with our effort! We're asking for a minimum of a $30 donation to enter the tournament. Please note that this donation is on a sliding scale- i.e. if you cannot afford to donate $30 then we are more than willing to accept whatever amount you can (in turn, if you are able to donate an amount greater than $30, we will most certainly accept that as well). We'll supply all the required materials (i.e. kegs), so just bring your game face (and your checkbook). And, as this is an open event, feel free to invite any and all of your friends who you think would be down for the cause. Sloshball not your thing? Don't worry, there will be sober opportunities to donate as well, so keep a lookout for the Fbook group invite that you all know is coming :)
